. including medieval Dutch and Flemish). The wife of  William the Conqueror , who bore this name, was the daughter of  Baldwin , Count of Flanders. In Flemish and Dutch the letter <i>-t-</i> was generally lost when it occurred between vowels, giving forms such as <i>Ma(h)auld</i>. <i>Maud</i> or <i>Matilda</i> was also the name of the daughter (  1102–67 ) of  Henry I  of England; she was married early in life to the Holy Roman Emperor  Henry V , and later disputed the throne of England with her cousin  Stephen . In  1128  she married  Geoffrey , Count of Anjou. A medieval chronicler commented, ‘she was a good woman, but she had little bliss with him’. The name <i>Maud</i> became quite common in England in the 19th century, when its popularity was influenced in part by  Tennyson's  poem Maud, published in  1855 , but has not been much used since the early decades of the 20th century."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Maud De Lowdham was born before 1366. She married Sir Thomas de Lowdham about 1377, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died after 1386."},"et":{"before 1366–after 1386":"enne 1366–pärast 1386","1346–1385":"1346–1385","1378–1428":"1378–1428","1366–1386":"1366–1386","1346":"1346","1378":"1378","before 1366":"enne 1366","1366":"1366","1386":"1386","1385":"1385","about 1377":"umbes 1377","after 1386":"pärast 1386","1428":"1428","Frenze, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Frenze, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England"},"fi":{"before 1366–after 1386":"ennen vuotta 1366–1386 jälkeen","1346–1385":"1346–1385","1378–1428":"1378–1428","1366–1386":"1366–1386","1346":"1346","1378":"1378","before 1366":"ennen vuotta 1366","1366":"1366","1386":"1386","1385":"1385","about 1377":"noin 1377","after 1386":"1386 jälkeen","1428":"1428","Frenze, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Frenze, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"England"},"fr":{"before 1366–after 1386":"avant 1366–après 1386","1346–1385":"1346–1385","1